ccess=true)` with a short\nsummary of how you solved it.\n\n## Workspace (read-only summary)\n```json\n{\n  \"OBJECTIVE.md\": {\n    \"_file\": \"OBJECTIVE.md\"\n  },\n  \"input\": {\n    \"_prep_dds.R\": {\n      \"_file\": \"_prep_dds.R\"\n    },\n    \"_prep_dds.log\": {\n      \"_file\": \"_prep_dds.log\"\n    },\n    \"_prep_normalized.tsv\": {\n      \"_file\": \"_prep_normalized.tsv\"\n    },\n    \"all_counts.tsv\": {\n      \"_file\": \"all_counts.tsv\"\n    },\n    \"dds.rds\": {\n      \"_file\": \"dds.rds\"\n    },\n    \"samples.tsv\": {\n      \"_file\": \"samples.tsv\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"meta.json\": {\n    \"_file\": \"meta.json\"\n  },\n  \"output\": {}\n}\n```\n\nSuccess hint: when `output/contrast_results.tsv` exists under the workspace, you may call submit_done(success=true).\n"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_vyRDr9qI8x94UV39mdQW0vt9", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"plan\": \"1. Load the DESeq2 object from the RDS file `input/dds.rds`.\\n2. Use the DESeq2 package to compute the results with the contrast `c('condition','ko','wt')` and set `alpha=0.05`.\\n3. Apply the `lfcShrink` function with `type='ashr'` to the results.\\n4. Sort the results by the adjusted p-value (`padj`).\\n5. Create a data frame with the columns `gene, baseMean, log2FoldChange, lfcSE, pvalue, padj`.\\n6. Write the data frame to a TSV file `output/contrast_results.tsv`.\\n7. Verify the existence of `output/contrast_results.tsv` and submit the task as done.\"}", "name": "write_plan"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "Wrote plan (549 chars) to .plan.md", "name": "write_plan", "tool_call_id": "call_vyRDr9qI8x94UV39mdQW0vt9"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_UO3EgP6aSm4V9Mkpf4ybSMMs", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"code\": \"library(DESeq2)\\nlibrary(ashr)\\n\\n# Load the DESeq2 object\\ndds <- readRDS('input/dds.rds')\\n\\n# C